        <!-- PostgreSQL Setup Section -->
        <section id="postgresql-setup" class="mb-16 animate-fadeIn">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-laser-blue flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-4">1</div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neural-charcoal">PostgreSQL Installation & Setup</h2>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 mb-8 border border-light-border">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-laser-blue">Step 1: Install PostgreSQL</h3>
                <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-6">
                    First, ensure PostgreSQL is installed on your system. Installation methods vary by operating system.
                </p>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">Installation Commands</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Ubuntu/Debian</span>
sudo apt update
sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib

<span class="code-comment"># CentOS/RHEL</span>
sudo yum install postgresql-server postgresql-contrib
sudo postgresql-setup initdb

<span class="code-comment"># macOS (Homebrew)</span>
brew install postgresql
brew services start postgresql

<span class="code-comment"># Windows - Download from https://www.postgresql.org/download/windows/</span></code></pre>
                </div>
                
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Step 2: Start PostgreSQL Service</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Start the PostgreSQL service and enable it to run on system boot.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">Start PostgreSQL Service</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Linux (Systemd)</span>
sudo systemctl start postgresql
sudo systemctl enable postgresql

<span class="code-comment"># Check status</span>
sudo systemctl status postgresql

<span class="code-comment"># macOS (Homebrew)</span>
brew services start postgresql

<span class="code-comment"># Windows - Start from Services Manager or use pg_ctl</span>
pg_ctl -D "C:\Program Files\PostgreSQL\15\data" start</code></pre>
                </div>
                
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Step 3: Create Database Administrator User</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Create a superuser with database creation privileges for your application.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">Create Admin User</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Access PostgreSQL as default postgres user</span>
sudo -u postgres psql

<span class="code-comment">-- Create a new role with superuser and database creation privileges</span>
CREATE ROLE admin WITH 
  LOGIN 
  SUPERUSER 
  CREATEDB 
  CREATEROLE 
  PASSWORD '<span class="code-variable">your_secure_password</span>';

<span class="code-comment">-- Verify the role was created</span>
\du

<span class="code-comment">-- Exit psql</span>
\q</code></pre>
                </div>
                
                <div class="info-box">
                    <h4 class="font-bold mb-2"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb mr-2"></i>Security Best Practice</h4>
                    <p>For production environments, create separate users with minimal required privileges instead of using a superuser. Consider creating:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 ml-4">
                        <li><strong>Application User:</strong> Basic read/write permissions</li>
                        <li><strong>Migration User:</strong> DDL permissions for migrations</li>
                        <li><strong>Backup User:</strong> Read-only permissions for backups</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Step 4: Create Application Database</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Create a dedicated database for your Dawn application.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">Create Database</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Connect as admin user</span>
psql -U admin -h localhost

<span class="code-comment">-- Create your application database</span>
CREATE DATABASE myapp_database 
  OWNER admin
  ENCODING 'UTF8'
  LC_COLLATE 'en_US.UTF-8'
  LC_CTYPE 'en_US.UTF-8'
  TEMPLATE template0;

<span class="code-comment">-- Connect to the new database</span>
\c myapp_database

<span class="code-comment">-- Verify connection and exit</span>
\dt
\q</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 border border-light-border">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-laser-blue">Optional: pgAdmin GUI Setup</h3>
                <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-6">
                    pgAdmin provides a graphical interface for managing your PostgreSQL databases.
                </p>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">Install pgAdmin</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Ubuntu/Debian</span>
sudo apt install pgadmin4

<span class="code-comment"># macOS (Homebrew)</span>
brew install --cask pgadmin4

<span class="code-comment"># Windows - Download from https://www.pgadmin.org/download/</span>

<span class="code-comment"># Or use web version</span>
sudo apt install pgadmin4-web
sudo /usr/pgadmin4/bin/setup-web.sh</code></pre>
                </div>
                
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Connecting to Database via pgAdmin</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Step-by-step guide to connect pgAdmin to your PostgreSQL database.</p>
                    
                    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside ml-4 space-y-2">
                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Launch pgAdmin</strong> from your applications or via web browser</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Right-click "Servers"</strong> → <strong>"Register"</strong> → <strong>"Server"</strong></li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>General Tab:</strong> Enter server name (e.g., "MyApp Development")</li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Connection Tab:</strong>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-6 mt-1">
                                <li>Host: <code>localhost</code> or <code>127.0.0.1</code></li>
                                <li>Port: <code>5432</code></li>
                                <li>Maintenance database: <code>postgres</code></li>
                                <li>Username: <code>admin</code></li>
                                <li>Password: <code>your_secure_password</code></li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Click "Save"</strong> to establish connection</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                
                <div class="success-box">
                    <h4 class="font-bold mb-2"><i class="fas fa-check-circle mr-2"></i>Connection Test</h4>
                    <p>Once connected, you should see your database in the object browser. You can expand it to view tables, run queries, and manage database objects visually.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Environment Configuration Section -->
        <section id="environment-config" class="mb-16 animate-fadeIn">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-build-green flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-4">2</div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neural-charcoal">Environment Configuration</h2>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 mb-8 border border-light-border">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-laser-blue">Database Configuration Files</h3>
                <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-6">
                    Configure your database connections for different environments (development, production, testing).
                </p>
                
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Step 5: Update Environment Files</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Create or update your environment configuration files with database connection details.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">dev.env - Development Environment</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Dawn Framework Development Environment</span>
<span class="code-comment"># Database Configuration</span>
DB_CONFIG={
  <span class="code-string">"host"</span>: <span class="code-string">"localhost"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"port"</span>: 5432,
  <span class="code-string">"user"</span>: <span class="code-string">"admin"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"password"</span>: <span class="code-string">"your_secure_password"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"dbname"</span>: <span class="code-string">"myapp_development"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"ssl"</span>: false,
  <span class="code-string">"max_connections"</span>: 20,
  <span class="code-string">"idle_timeout"</span>: 30000
}

<span class="code-comment"># Connection string format (alternative)</span>
DB_CONNECTION_STRING=<span class="code-string">"host=localhost port=5432 user=admin password=your_secure_password dbname=myapp_development sslmode=disable"</span>

<span class="code-comment"># Application Settings</span>
APP_PORT=8080
APP_ENV=development
LOG_LEVEL=debug</code></pre>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">prod.env - Production Environment</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Dawn Framework Production Environment</span>
<span class="code-comment"># Database Configuration</span>
DB_CONFIG={
  <span class="code-string">"host"</span>: <span class="code-string">"production-db.example.com"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"port"</span>: 5432,
  <span class="code-string">"user"</span>: <span class="code-string">"myapp_prod_user"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"password"</span>: <span class="code-string">"${DB_PASSWORD}"</span>, <span class="code-comment"># Use environment variable for security</span>
  <span class="code-string">"dbname"</span>: <span class="code-string">"myapp_production"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"ssl"</span>: true,
  <span class="code-string">"ssl_ca"</span>: <span class="code-string">"/path/to/ca-certificate.crt"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"max_connections"</span>: 50,
  <span class="code-string">"idle_timeout"</span>: 30000
}

<span class="code-comment"># Connection string format</span>
DB_CONNECTION_STRING=<span class="code-string">"host=production-db.example.com port=5432 user=myapp_prod_user password=${DB_PASSWORD} dbname=myapp_production sslmode=verify-full"</span>

<span class="code-comment"># Application Settings</span>
APP_PORT=8080
APP_ENV=production
LOG_LEVEL=info</code></pre>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">test.env - Testing Environment</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Dawn Framework Testing Environment</span>
DB_CONFIG={
  <span class="code-string">"host"</span>: <span class="code-string">"localhost"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"port"</span>: 5432,
  <span class="code-string">"user"</span>: <span class="code-string">"admin"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"password"</span>: <span class="code-string">"your_secure_password"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"dbname"</span>: <span class="code-string">"myapp_test"</span>,
  <span class="code-string">"ssl"</span>: false,
  <span class="code-string">"max_connections"</span>: 10
}

DB_CONNECTION_STRING=<span class="code-string">"host=localhost port=5432 user=admin password=your_secure_password dbname=myapp_test sslmode=disable"</span>

APP_PORT=8081
APP_ENV=test
LOG_LEVEL=warn</code></pre>
                </div>
                
                <div class="warning-box mt-6">
                    <h4 class="font-bold mb-2"><i class="fas fa-shield-alt mr-2"></i>Security Important</h4>
                    <p>Never commit passwords or sensitive information to version control. Use environment variables for production credentials and ensure your <code>.env</code> files are included in <code>.gitignore</code>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Migrations Section -->
        <section id="migrations" class="mb-16 animate-fadeIn">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-query-purple flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold mr-4">3</div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neural-charcoal">Database Migrations</h2>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 mb-8 border border-light-border">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-laser-blue">Model Creation & Migration Workflow</h3>
                <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-6">
                    Learn how to create models and manage database schema changes using Dawn's migration system.
                </p>
                
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Step 6: Create Your Data Model</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Define your data structure using Dawn's ORM model system.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">Example: User Model (models/user.lua)</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-keyword">local</span> Model = <span class="code-keyword">require</span>(<span class="code-string">"path.to.model"</span>)

<span class="code-keyword">local</span> User = Model:<span class="code-type">extend</span>(<span class="code-string">"users"</span>, {
    id = <span class="code-string">"integer"</span>,
    username = <span class="code-string">"string"</span>,
    email = <span class="code-string">"string"</span>,
    password_hash = <span class="code-string">"string"</span>,
    first_name = <span class="code-string">"string"</span>,
    last_name = <span class="code-string">"string"</span>,
    is_active = <span class="code-string">"boolean"</span>,
    created_at = <span class="code-string">"timestamp"</span>,
    updated_at = <span class="code-string">"timestamp"</span>
}, {
    _primary_key = <span class="code-string">"id"</span>,
    _timestamps = true,
    _unique_keys = {
        {<span class="code-string">"email"</span>},
        {<span class="code-string">"username"</span>}
    },
    _indexes = {
        <span class="code-string">"email"</span>,
        {<span class="code-string">"last_name"</span>, <span class="code-string">"first_name"</span>}
    }
})

<span class="code-keyword">return</span> User</code></pre>
                </div>
                
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Step 7: Generate Migration File</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Create a migration file based on your model definition.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">Generate Migration Command</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Generate migration for users table</span>
dawn generate migration users

<span class="code-comment"># Generate migration for specific model</span>
dawn generate migration create_loans_table


<span class="code-comment"># Output: Created migration: db/migrations/20231010120000_create_users_table.lua</span></code></pre>
                </div>
                
             
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Step 8: Run Migrations</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Execute the migration to create or modify your database schema.</p>
                </div>
                
