                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neural-charcoal">Troubleshooting & Common Issues</h2>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 border border-light-border">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-laser-blue">Common Problems and Solutions</h3>
                
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div class="warning-box">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Connection Refused Errors</h4>
                        <p><strong>Problem:</strong> <code>psql: could not connect to server: Connection refused</code></p>
                        <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2">
                            <li>Ensure PostgreSQL service is running: <code>sudo systemctl status postgresql</code></li>
                            <li>Check if PostgreSQL is listening on correct port: <code>sudo netstat -tulpn | grep 5432</code></li>
                            <li>Verify <code>pg_hba.conf</code> allows connections from your IP</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="warning-box">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Authentication Failures</h4>
                        <p><strong>Problem:</strong> <code>password authentication failed for user "admin"</code></p>
                        <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2">
                            <li>Verify password in <code>.env</code> files matches PostgreSQL user password</li>
                            <li>Check <code>pg_hba.conf</code> authentication method for your user</li>
                            <li>Reset password: <code>ALTER USER admin WITH PASSWORD 'newpassword';</code></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="warning-box">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Database Does Not Exist</h4>
                        <p><strong>Problem:</strong> <code>database "myapp_development" does not exist</code></p>
                        <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2">
                            <li>Create the database: <code>CREATE DATABASE myapp_development;</code></li>
                            <li>Check database name spelling in <code>.env</code> file</li>
                            <li>Verify user has access to the database</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="warning-box">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Migration Failures</h4>
                        <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Migration fails with syntax errors or constraint violations</p>
                        <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2">
                            <li>Check migration file for SQL syntax errors</li>
                            <li>Verify table doesn't already exist before creating</li>
                            <li>Use <code>IF NOT EXISTS</code> for table and index creation</li>
                            <li>Run migrations in transaction mode for easy rollback</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="info-box">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Useful Diagnostic Commands</h4>
                        <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 code-block mt-2">
                            <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment"># Check PostgreSQL service status</span>
sudo systemctl status postgresql

<span class="code-comment"># Check active connections</span>
sudo -u postgres psql -c "SELECT datname, usename, application_name, client_addr FROM pg_stat_activity;"

<span class="code-comment"># List all databases</span>
sudo -u postgres psql -c "\l"

<span class="code-comment"># List all users</span>
sudo -u postgres psql -c "\du"

<span class="code-comment"># Check table sizes and row counts</span>
sudo -u postgres psql -d myapp_development -c "\dt+"

<span class="code-comment"># View PostgreSQL logs</span>
sudo tail -f /var/log/postgresql/postgresql-*.log</code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
